        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 12:27AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1226 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
over Gladys, or 8 miles south of Rustburg, moving east at 25 mph.
Numerous other storms were located near Hixburg, Toga, Centenary,
and Charlotte Court House.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Buckingham...
Appomattox...
Brookneal...
Keysville...
Charlotte Court House...
Dillwyn...
and Phenix.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
